 {"id":"wa-3cyp.2","title":"Performance integration test suite — 30+ tests, mock mux server, error injection","description":"## Goal
Integration test suite that validates all performance improvements work correctly in concert — connection pool under load, timeout hardening against real zombie scenarios, protocol recovery from actual error states, watchdog monitoring, and cache GC effectiveness.

## Background & Motivation
Unit tests verify individual components. Benchmarks measure speed. Integration tests verify components work TOGETHER correctly:
- Does the connection pool actually prevent zombie CLI processes? (bd-41w + bd-6js)
- Does protocol recovery actually reconnect after a UnexpectedResponse? (wa-2c50 + bd-41w)
- Does the watchdog detect and restart a stuck mux server? (wa-2cha)
- Does tiered capture + notification coalescing work together without dropping events? (bd-9dp + wa-x4rq)
- Does cache GC run without disrupting active captures? (wa-1nkt)
- Does scrollback pressure eviction integrate with content-addressable dedup? (wa-3r5e + wa-n9cp)

## Test Modules

### 1. Connection Pool Integration (tests bd-41w)
**File**: `crates/wa-core/tests/integration/pool_tests.rs`
```rust
// Pool lifecycle: create pool, acquire N connections, return, acquire again
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_lifecycle()
// Pool under load: 50 concurrent requests through 8-connection pool
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_under_load()
// Pool stale connection: connection goes bad, pool replaces it
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_stale_connection_recovery()
// Pool exhaustion: all connections busy, new request waits then succeeds
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_exhaustion_wait()
// Pool metrics: verify connection count, wait times, error rates tracked
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_metrics_accuracy()
```

### 2. Timeout & Zombie Prevention (tests bd-6js)
**File**: `crates/wa-core/tests/integration/timeout_tests.rs`
```rust
// Timeout kills: operation exceeding deadline is killed
#[tokio::test] async fn timeout_kills_slow_operation()
// Orphan detection: process outlives parent, reaper finds it
#[tokio::test] async fn orphan_reaper_detects_zombie()
// Clean shutdown: normal operation completes without timeout
#[tokio::test] async fn clean_shutdown_no_timeout()
// Cascading timeout: pool + timeout work together
#[tokio::test] async fn pool_with_timeout_integration()
```

### 3. Protocol Recovery Integration (tests wa-2c50)
**File**: `crates/wa-core/tests/integration/protocol_tests.rs`
```rust
// Error injection: send bad PDU, verify recovery
#[tokio::test] async fn recover_from_unexpected_response()
// Reconnect: connection drops, auto-reconnect succeeds
#[tokio::test] async fn auto_reconnect_on_drop()
// Retry logic: transient error retried, permanent error surfaced
#[tokio::test] async fn retry_transient_error()
// Backoff: exponential backoff between reconnection attempts
#[tokio::test] async fn exponential_backoff_timing()
// Circuit breaker: too many failures stops retrying temporarily
#[tokio::test] async fn circuit_breaker_activation()
```

### 4. Watchdog Integration (tests wa-2cha)
**File**: `crates/wa-core/tests/integration/watchdog_tests.rs`
```rust
// Health check: healthy mux server passes check
#[tokio::test] async fn watchdog_healthy_server()
// Unhealthy detection: unresponsive server flagged
#[tokio::test] async fn watchdog_detects_unresponsive()
// Alert emission: unhealthy state emits alert event
#[tokio::test] async fn watchdog_emits_alert()
// Metric tracking: response times, success rates, uptime
#[tokio::test] async fn watchdog_metrics()
```

### 5. Capture Pipeline Integration (tests bd-9dp + wa-x4rq)
**File**: `crates/wa-core/tests/integration/capture_tests.rs`
```rust
// Tiered rates: active pane polled more often than idle
